The DP’s director of communication Emmanuel Tallam confirmed to the Nation that the deceased was a prison warden who was under the press unit.
“The deceased was not in the DP's security team but was a prison officer working as a driver in our communication team,” said Mr Tallam.
Mr Too’s death comes barely a year after Sergeant Kipyegon Kenei, an officer attached to the Deputy President's office, who was believed to have been a key witness in the fake Sh39 billion arms deal, died mysteriously. Police are suspecting a murder-suicide. His wife was rushed to the Kenyatta National Hospital in serious condition. The footbridge was damaged by a trailer carrying an excavator earlier in December 2020. However they made us feel, the men and women in this list elicited different emotions in all of us.